<h2>Tips for Ordering Samples</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Order early in the design process</strong> â€” Give your customer something to hold and compare during the initial consultation. Physical samples close more deals than catalog images.</li>
  <li><strong>Request the exact finish and door style</strong> â€” Generic samples don't build confidence. Match the sample to the spec you're presenting.</li>
  <li><strong>Keep a showroom sample library</strong> â€” Maintain a curated set of your most-ordered styles and finishes so you have them on hand for walk-ins.</li>
  <li><strong>Use samples to upsell</strong> â€” Show the difference between standard and premium finishes side by side. Let the quality speak for itself.</li>
</ul>

